Section 1:
1 L.D. 120
2 Date: (Filing No. S- )
3 CRIMINAL JUSTICE AND PUBLIC SAFETY
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 SENATE
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 36, L.D. 120, “An Act to Expand the
10 Membership of the Homeland Security Advisory Council”
11 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
12 following:
13 'Sec. 1. 37-B MRSA §708, sub-§1, as amended by PL 2011, c. 529, §1 and
14 amended by c. 657, Pt. W, §6, is further amended to read:
15 1. Membership. The council is composed of the following 9 11 members:
16 A. The director or the director's designee;
17 B. The Commissioner of Defense, Veterans and Emergency Management or the
18 commissioner's designee;
19 C. The Commissioner of Public Safety or the commissioner's designee;
20 D. The Director of the Maine Center for Disease Control and Prevention within the
21 Department of Health and Human Services or the director's designee;
22 E. The Chief of the State Police within the Department of Public Safety or the chief's
23 designee;
24 F. A representative of the Governor;
25 G. The Commissioner of Inland Fisheries and Wildlife or the commissioner's designee;
26 H. The Commissioner of Marine Resources or the commissioner's designee; and
27 I. The Commissioner of Agriculture, Conservation and Forestry or the commissioner's
28 designee.;
29 J. The Chief Information Officer of the Office of Information Technology within the
30 Department of Administrative and Financial Services or the officer's designee; and
31 K. The director of the Maine School Safety Center established within the Department
32 of Education or the director's designee.
Page 1 - 132LR0184(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 36, L.D. 120
1 The director is the chair of the council. The Commissioner of Defense, Veterans and
2 Emergency Management is the advisor of the council. Commissioner designees must be
3 uniformed law enforcement personnel.'
4 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
5 number to read consecutively.
6 SUMMARY
77 This amendment changes the membership of the Homeland Security Advisory Council
88 by including the designee of any ex officio member.
99 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
1100 (See attached)
Page 2 - 132LR0184(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
